HEADWORD: Tetrachord
<hw>Tet"ra*chord</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tetrachordon</ets>, Gr. <?/, from <?/ four-stringed;
<grk>te`tra-</grk> (see <er>Tetra-</er>) + <?/ a chord: cf. F.
<ets>t⟦eacute⟧trachorde</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anc. Mus.)</fld> <def>A
